---
title: Lemon Butter Sockeye Salmon with Asparagus Amandine and Horseradish Potato Mash
description: Looking for a meal that’s light, bright, and super satisfying? You’ve come to the right place! This dish is all that and then some. Salmon fillets are pan-seared and served alongside horseradish and chive-flecked mashed potatoes and asparagus amandine (that’s French for “tossed with some toasted almonds”). For a dynamic finish, the salmon is drizzled with a buttery, lemony pan sauce. You’ll definitely want to keep this delicious recipe in your back pocket for the next time you’re craving some Parisian fare.
